<subSubSection id="BCF1654AFFEEFFB6FDBCFBC0A86DFA7D" pageId="8" pageNumber="100" type="description">
<paragraph id="F45436C1FFEEFFB6FDBCFBC0AF81FA94" blockId="8.[136,1452,1091,2021]" pageId="8" pageNumber="100">
<emphasis id="C69FEAD3FFEEFFB6FDBCFBC0AC7DFB98" bold="true" box="[136,284,1091,1117]" pageId="8" pageNumber="100">Description:</emphasis>
Robust grass, 
<quantity id="33139B24FFEEFFB6FCFEFBC7AF3DFB9B" box="[458,604,1092,1118]" metricMagnitude="0" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.5" metricValueMax="2.0" metricValueMin="1.0" pageId="8" pageNumber="100" unit="cm" value="150.0" valueMax="200.0" valueMin="100.0">100–200 cm</quantity>
. Culms with 3–5 brown and glabrous nodes. Ligules obtuse. Leaf-blades 
<quantity id="33139B24FFEEFFB6FDBCFBE5AD9BFB44" box="[136,250,1126,1153]" metricMagnitude="-1" metricUnit="m" metricValue="4.0" metricValueMax="6.0" metricValueMin="2.0" pageId="8" pageNumber="100" unit="cm" value="40.0" valueMax="60.0" valueMin="20.0">20–60 cm</quantity>
× (5)8–9(14) mm, convolute, glabrous or scaberulous adaxially and scabrous abaxially. Panicle 9–26 × 
<quantity id="33139B24FFEEFFB6FDBCFB0AAC6DFB66" box="[136,268,1161,1187]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.1" metricValueMax="3.3" metricValueMin="0.9" pageId="8" pageNumber="100" unit="cm" value="2.1" valueMax="3.3" valueMin="0.9">0.9–3.3 cm</quantity>
, spiciform, dense, linear, interrupted at the base and narrowing towards the apex. Lower branches of the inflorescence adpressed. Rhachis and branches scabrous and short. Spikelets 
<quantity id="33139B24FFEEFFB6F92AFB28A91EFB03" box="[1054,1151,1195,1222]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="6.0" metricValueMax="7.0" metricValueMin="5.0" pageId="8" pageNumber="100" unit="mm" value="6.0" valueMax="7.0" valueMin="5.0">5–7 mm</quantity>
, oblong. Glumes ovate, 3- veined. Midvein scabrous and lateral veins interrupted in the middle. Lower glume 
<quantity id="33139B24FFEEFFB6F90CFB4DA9F9FB2C" box="[1080,1176,1230,1257]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="5.5" metricValueMax="7.0" metricValueMin="4.0" pageId="8" pageNumber="100" unit="mm" value="5.5" valueMax="7.0" valueMin="4.0">4–7 mm</quantity>
, shorter than or equal to the florets. Upper glume 
<quantity id="33139B24FFEEFFB6FCABFB72AF72FACE" box="[415,531,1265,1292]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="5.75" metricValueMax="7.0" metricValueMin="4.5" pageId="8" pageNumber="100" unit="mm" value="5.75" valueMax="7.0" valueMin="4.5">4.5–7 mm</quantity>
. Lemma of male florets 
<quantity id="33139B24FFEEFFB6FE16FB72AEE1FACE" box="[802,896,1265,1292]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="6.0" metricValueMax="7.0" metricValueMin="5.0" pageId="8" pageNumber="100" unit="mm" value="6.0" valueMax="7.0" valueMin="5.0">5–7 mm</quantity>
, membranaceous, scabrous. Awn 
<quantity id="33139B24FFEEFFB6F9C2FB72A81CFACE" box="[1270,1405,1265,1292]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.0" metricValueMax="1.5" metricValueMin="0.5" pageId="8" pageNumber="100" unit="mm" value="1.0" valueMax="1.5" valueMin="0.5">0.5–1.5 mm</quantity>
and apically inserted. Lemma of lower male floret elliptic, 1-keeled, 5-veined. Lemma of upper male floret oblong. Lemma of apical female floret 
<quantity id="33139B24FFEEFFB6FCB3FAB5ACABFA94" box="[391,458,1334,1361]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="4.0" pageId="8" pageNumber="100" unit="mm" value="4.0">4 mm</quantity>
, muticous or mucronate.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="F45436C1FFEEFFB6FD89FADAAF1EFA50" blockId="8.[136,1452,1091,2021]" pageId="8" pageNumber="100">
<emphasis id="C69FEAD3FFEEFFB6FD89FADAAC0AFAB6" bold="true" box="[189,363,1369,1395]" pageId="8" pageNumber="100">Leaf anatomy:</emphasis>
Long cells 190–240 μm long. Stomata 36–42 μm, in adaxial surface. Bulliform cells present. Leaf section closed with 28–30 quadrangular ribs.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="F45436C1FFEEFFB6FD89FA1DA86DFA7D" blockId="8.[136,1452,1091,2021]" box="[189,1292,1438,1465]" pageId="8" pageNumber="100">
