<paragraph id="F45436C1FFEEFFB6FD89F930AE89F820" blockId="8.[136,1452,1091,2021]" pageId="8" pageNumber="100">
<emphasis id="C69FEAD3FFEEFFB6FD89F930AC04F908" bold="true" box="[189,357,1715,1741]" pageId="8" pageNumber="100">Observations:</emphasis>
No reference to any particular specimen is included in the protologue of 
<taxonomicName id="33EB4D42FFEEFFB6F9FAF937A8C5F908" authorityName="Ruiz &amp; Pavon" authorityYear="1798" box="[1230,1444,1715,1741]" class="Liliopsida" family="Poaceae" genus="Torresia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" order="Poales" pageId="8" pageNumber="100" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="utriculata">
<emphasis id="C69FEAD3FFEEFFB6F9FAF937A8C5F908" box="[1230,1444,1715,1741]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="100">Torresia utriculata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, where only the region of collection is mentioned. One specimen collected by Ruiz &amp; Pavón is stored in the Real Jardín Botánico de Madrid Herbarium (MA), but no locality is included in the label. 
<bibRefCitation id="907A4B30FFEEFFB6FED8F97AA9E7F8D6" author="Parodi, L. R." box="[1004,1158,1785,1811]" pageId="8" pageNumber="100" pagination="183 - 212" refId="ref10950" refString="Parodi, L. R. (1941) Revision de las gramineas sudamericanas del genero Hierochloe. Revista del Museo de La Plata (N. S.) 3 (14): 183 - 212." type="journal article" year="1941">Parodi (1941)</bibRefCitation>
highlighted this specimen as the “type”, but no correct typification was carried out [Article 
<quantity id="33139B24FFEEFFB6FE46F89FAEA0F8F0" box="[882,961,1819,1846]" metricMagnitude="-1" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.3114" pageId="8" pageNumber="100" unit="in" value="9.1">9.10 in</quantity>
<bibRefCitation id="907A4B30FFEEFFB6FEFDF898A9DAF8F3" author="Turland, N. J. &amp; Wiersema, J. H. &amp; Barrie, F. R. &amp; Greuter, W. &amp; Hawksworth, D. L. &amp; Herendeen, P. S. &amp; Knapp, S. &amp; Kusber, W. - H. &amp; Li, D. - Z. &amp; Marhold, K. &amp; May, T. W. &amp; McNeill, J. &amp; Monro, A. M. &amp; Prado, J. &amp; Price, M. J. &amp; Smith, G. F." box="[969,1211,1819,1846]" pageId="8" pageNumber="100" refId="ref11638" refString="Turland, N. J., Wiersema, J. H., Barrie, F. R., Greuter, W., Hawksworth, D. L., Herendeen, P. S., Knapp, S., Kusber, W. - H., Li, D. - Z., Marhold, K., May, T. W., McNeill, J., Monro, A. M., Prado, J., Price, M. J. &amp; Smith, G. F. (Eds.) (2018) International Code of Nomenclature for algae, fungi, and plants (Shenzhen Code) adopted by the Nineteenth International Botanical Congress Shenzhen, China, July 2017. [Regnum Vegetabile 159] Glashutten: Koeltz Botanical Books, 254 pp. https: // doi. org / 10.12705 / Code. 2018" type="book" year="2018">
Turland 
<emphasis id="C69FEAD3FFEEFFB6F91DF89FA93DF8F0" box="[1065,1116,1819,1845]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="100">et al</emphasis>
. (2018)
</bibRefCitation>
]. Plants conserved in the Dombey and Jussieu Herbaria at the Muséum National d’Histoire Naturelle de Paris (P, sub 
<emphasis id="C69FEAD3FFEEFFB6F9E4F8BCA8CAF89D" box="[1232,1451,1854,1880]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="100">
<taxonomicName id="33EB4D42FFEEFFB6F9E4F8BCA8C6F89D" authorityName="Ruiz &amp; Pavon" authorityYear="1798" box="[1232,1447,1854,1880]" class="Liliopsida" family="Poaceae" genus="Torresia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" order="Poales" pageId="8" pageNumber="100" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="utriculata">Torresia utriculata</taxonomicName>
,
</emphasis>
P-31093, P-01931094 and P-00661399, the latter with a label that reads “ 
<collectingCountry id="8CFC7651FFEEFFB6FEF2F8E2A965F8BE" box="[966,1028,1889,1915]" name="Chile" pageId="8" pageNumber="100">Chili</collectingCountry>
. Herb. Dombey”) were considered as duplicates by Parodi (l.c.), since Dombey travelled alongside Ruíz &amp; Pavón to 
<collectingCountry id="8CFC7651FFEEFFB6F920F807A926F85B" box="[1044,1095,1924,1950]" name="Peru" pageId="8" pageNumber="100">Peru</collectingCountry>
and 
<collectingCountry id="8CFC7651FFEEFFB6F9B6F800A9A3F858" box="[1154,1218,1923,1949]" name="Chile" pageId="8" pageNumber="100">Chile</collectingCountry>
. It is not possible to know, however, the exact material used to describe the species, so the specimen from MA should be considered the 
<typeStatus id="2B508863FFEEFFB6FDBCF849AD8EF821" box="[136,239,1994,2020]" pageId="8" pageNumber="100">lectotype</typeStatus>
[Article 9.17, Recommendation 9A (1&amp;2) in 
<bibRefCitation id="907A4B30FFEEFFB6FFDBF849AEBDF820" author="Turland, N. J. &amp; Wiersema, J. H. &amp; Barrie, F. R. &amp; Greuter, W. &amp; Hawksworth, D. L. &amp; Herendeen, P. S. &amp; Knapp, S. &amp; Kusber, W. - H. &amp; Li, D. - Z. &amp; Marhold, K. &amp; May, T. W. &amp; McNeill, J. &amp; Monro, A. M. &amp; Prado, J. &amp; Price, M. J. &amp; Smith, G. F." box="[751,988,1994,2021]" pageId="8" pageNumber="100" refId="ref11638" refString="Turland, N. J., Wiersema, J. H., Barrie, F. R., Greuter, W., Hawksworth, D. L., Herendeen, P. S., Knapp, S., Kusber, W. - H., Li, D. - Z., Marhold, K., May, T. W., McNeill, J., Monro, A. M., Prado, J., Price, M. J. &amp; Smith, G. F. (Eds.) (2018) International Code of Nomenclature for algae, fungi, and plants (Shenzhen Code) adopted by the Nineteenth International Botanical Congress Shenzhen, China, July 2017. [Regnum Vegetabile 159] Glashutten: Koeltz Botanical Books, 254 pp. https: // doi. org / 10.12705 / Code. 2018" type="book" year="2018">
Turland 
<emphasis id="C69FEAD3FFEEFFB6FE79F848AE1FF821" box="[845,894,1994,2020]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="100">et al</emphasis>
. (2018)
</bibRefCitation>
].
</paragraph>
